@Señor Poodles You have no idea what you're talking about. You probably read some article about people who did microservices wrong or have a shallow understanding. This video actually is much more valuable than it seems at first and educates you on one of the things to do properly with microservices / distributed systems: metrics, logs, and tracing.

This is a topic so many people get wrong (just like microservices or Service-oriented Architecture).

And FYI, people have been using microservices and soa way before modern web. Read about CQRS, Domain-driven Design, and event sourcing to get a handle on how to manage that type of architecture and not re-invent the wheel like Uber did.
